cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with error-correcting codes and decoding algorithms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses a simple construction of linear codes and a fast decoding algorithm. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is a possibility as the paper mentions the running time of the decoder and its potential applications in group testing. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper mentions an application of the techniques in non-adaptive group testing. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possibility as the paper discusses the computation of the syndrome from a received word in nearly linear time.
